<font color="#FF0000">DOCTOR SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Mon Dec 16 14:19:00 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Well Doctor, it appears that like a lot of Vietnam era folks ; you too, are passionate.  I don't or won't acknowledge your concepts of patriotism.  Even today I recall reading about people my age protesting the war.  All I can say 30 years later is that my views haven't changed much about folks who were &quot;anti-war&quot;.  It is kind of sad that while you cleaned bedpans, I was up to armpits in the stuff you were dumping out.  It would have been nice if you could have experienced the homecoming that alot of us warriors recieved.  How I longed to see a side walk, see a round eyed woman, smell the pine trees.  It appears that as a patriot you got to do these things.  So I recognize you.  I don't accept you, but I recognize you.
<p><code>-- cbotkins@visuallink.com  (Chet Botkins) </code><p>


